33-- ----------------------  some
34
35-- | Construct relmap of existential filter.
36consSome :: (Ord c) => C.RopCons c
37consSome med = 
38    do rmap <- Rop.getRelmap med "-relmap"
39       Right $ relmapSome med rmap
40
41-- | Relmap of existential filter.
42relmapSome :: (Ord c) => C.Intmed c -> O.Map (C.Relmap c)
43relmapSome med = C.relmapBinary med relkitSome
44
45-- | Calculate existential filter.
46relkitSome :: (Ord c) => C.RelkitBinary c
47relkitSome = relkitSemi False
48
49relkitSemi :: (Ord c) => Bool -> C.RelkitBinary c
50relkitSemi isEmpty (C.Relkit _ _ kitb2) he1 =
51    Right $ C.relkit he1 $ C.RelkitAbSemi p kitb2
52    where p bo2 = Right $ null bo2 == isEmpty
53
54
55
56-- ----------------------  none
57
58-- | Construct relmap of non-existential filter.
59consNone :: (Ord c) => C.RopCons c
60consNone med =
61    do rmap <- Rop.getRelmap med "-relmap"
62       Right $ relmapNone med rmap
63
64-- | Relmap of non-existential filter.
65relmapNone :: (Ord c) => C.Intmed c -> O.Map (C.Relmap c)
66relmapNone med = C.relmapBinary med relkitNone
67
68-- | Calculate non-existential filter.
69relkitNone :: (Ord c) => C.RelkitBinary c
70relkitNone = relkitSemi True
71

74-- ----------------------  some-meet & none-meet
75
76-- | Construct some-and-meet relmap.
77consSomeMeet :: (Ord c) => C.RopCons c
78consSomeMeet med =
79    do rmap <- Rop.getRelmap med "-relmap"
80       sh   <- Rop.getMaybe Rop.getTerms med "-share"
81       Right $ relmapSomeMeet med sh rmap
82
83-- | Some-and-meet relmap.
84--
85--   @some-meet R == some ( meet R )@
86relmapSomeMeet :: (Ord c) => C.Intmed c -> Rop.SharedTerms -> C.Relmap c -> C.Relmap c
87relmapSomeMeet med sh = C.relmapBinary med $ relkitFilterMeet True sh
88
89-- | Construct none-and-meet relmap.
90consNoneMeet :: (Ord c) => C.RopCons c
91consNoneMeet med =
92    do rmap <- Rop.getRelmap med "-relmap"
93       sh   <- Rop.getMaybe Rop.getTerms med "-share"
94       Right $ relmapNoneMeet med sh rmap
95
96-- | None-and-meet relmap.
97--
98--   @ none-meet R == none ( meet R ) @
99relmapNoneMeet :: (Ord c) => C.Intmed c -> Rop.SharedTerms -> C.Relmap c -> C.Relmap c
100relmapNoneMeet med sh = C.relmapBinary med $ relkitFilterMeet False sh
101
102relkitFilterMeet :: forall c. (Ord c) => Bool -> Rop.SharedTerms -> C.RelkitBinary c
103relkitFilterMeet which sh (C.Relkit _ (Just he2) kitb2) (Just he1) = kit3 where
104    lr     = D.termPicker he1 he2
105    kit3   = case Rop.unmatchShare sh lr of
106               Nothing     -> Right $ C.relkitJust he1 $ C.RelkitAbFull False kitf3 [kitb2]
107               Just (e, a) -> Msg.unmatchShare e a
108
109    kitf3 :: [C.BodyMap c] -> C.BodyMap c
110    kitf3 bmaps bo1 =
111        do let [bmap2] = bmaps
112           bo2 <- bmap2 bo1
113           Right $ test (toSet bo2) `filter` bo1
114
115    toSet = Set.fromList . map (D.ssRShare lr)
116    test b2set cs1 = D.ssLShare lr cs1 `Set.member` b2set == which
117
118relkitFilterMeet _ _ _ _ = Right C.relkitNothing
119
120
121-- ----------------------  sub
122
123-- | Construct relmap for subrelation filter.
124consSub :: (Ord c) => C.RopCons c
125consSub med =
126    do rmap <- Rop.getRelmap med "-relmap"
127       sh   <- Rop.getMaybe Rop.getTerms med "-share"
128       Right $ relmapSub med sh rmap
129
130-- | Relmap for subrelation filter.
131relmapSub :: (Ord c) => C.Intmed c -> Rop.SharedTerms -> O.Map (C.Relmap c)
132relmapSub med sh = C.relmapBinary med $ relkitSub sh
133
134-- | Calculate subrelation filter.
135relkitSub :: (Ord c) => Rop.SharedTerms -> C.RelkitBinary c
136relkitSub sh kit2@(C.Relkit _ (Just he2) _) he1'@(Just he1)
137    | he1 `D.isSuperhead` he2 = kit
138    | otherwise = case Rop.unmatchShare sh lr of
139                    Nothing     -> Right $ C.relkitJust he1 $ C.RelkitConst []
140                    Just (e, a) -> Msg.unmatchShare e a
141    where
142      lr  = D.termPicker he1 he2
143      kit = relkitFilterMeet True sh kit2 he1'
144
145relkitSub _ _ _ = Right C.relkitNothing
146
147
148
149-- ----------------------  compose
150
151-- | Construct relmap for relational composition.
152consCompose :: (Ord c) => C.RopCons c
153consCompose med =
154    do rmap <- Rop.getRelmap med "-relmap"
155       sh   <- Rop.getMaybe Rop.getTerms med "-share"
156       Right $ relmapCompose med sh rmap
157
158-- | Relational composition.
159relmapCompose :: (Ord c) => C.Intmed c -> Rop.SharedTerms -> O.Map (C.Relmap c)
160relmapCompose med sh = C.relmapBinary med $ relkitCompose Rop.relkitMeet sh
161
162-- | Calculate relational composition.
163relkitCompose :: forall c. (Ord c) => (Rop.SharedTerms -> C.RelkitBinary c) -> Rop.SharedTerms -> C.RelkitBinary c
164relkitCompose m sh kit2@(C.Relkit _ (Just he2) _) (Just he1) =
165    do kitMeet <- m sh kit2 (Just he1)
166       kitCut  <- Rop.relkitCut (sharedNames he1 he2) (C.relkitOutput kitMeet)
167       Right (kitMeet B.<> kitCut)
168relkitCompose _ _ _ _ = Right C.relkitNothing
169
170sharedNames :: D.Head -> D.Head -> [S.TermName]
171sharedNames he1 he2 = shared where
172    ns1     = D.getTermNames he1
173    ns2     = D.getTermNames he2
174    lr      = D.termPicker ns1 ns2
175    shared  = D.ssRShare lr ns2
